Gnathosoma ( Figs 2B – D ) — Generally, morphology is typical for Microzetidae ( Grandjean 1936 ; Engelbrecht 1972 ;
Ermilov et al. 2013
). Subcapitulum slightly longer than wide (57 – 65 × 53 – 61). Subcapitular setae ( h , m , a ) setiform, barbed, similar in length (16). Two pairs of adoral setae ( or 1 , or 2 ) minute (4), thin, smooth. Palps (53) with nine setae and one solenidion (+ω) on palptarsi. Chelicerae (61 – 65) with two setiform setae: cha (20 – 24) ciliate unilaterally, chb shorter (16), barbed. Cheliceral tubercles (6 – 8) thorn-like, blunt-ended.

